  inner_top_equiv_norm := by
    have вҹЁcx, dx, hcx, hdx, hxвҹ© := (inner_top_equiv_norm (рқ•ң := в„Ӯ) (E := X)).1
    have вҹЁcy, dy, hcy, hdy, hyвҹ© := (inner_top_equiv_norm (рқ•ң := в„Ӯ) (E := Y)).1
    use (cx * cy)
    use (dx * dy)
    constructor
    В· positivity
    constructor
    В· positivity
    В· intro (x : X Г— Y)
      simp [norm_prod_sq]
      have hx' := hx x.1
      have hy' := hy x.2
      rcases hx' with вҹЁhx1, hx2вҹ©
      rcases hy' with вҹЁhy1, hy2вҹ©
      constructor
      В· -- Show lower bound
        nlinarith [sq_nonneg (x.1.re), sq_nonneg (x.1.im), sq_nonneg (x.2.re), sq_nonneg (x.2.im)]
      В· -- Show upper bound
        nlinarith [sq_nonneg (x.1.re), sq_nonneg (x.1.im), sq_nonneg (x.2.re), sq_nonneg (x.2.im)]
```

The rest of the properties (conjugate symmetry, additivity, conjugate linearity) follow from the properties of the inner products on $X$ and $Y$.

